Name: Solgaleo
Summary: Solgaleo is a Psychic/Steel Legendary Pokémon native to the Alola region. Honored and feared as the "beast that devours the sun", Solgaleo is known for its incredible power and its striking mane that can light up the darkest of night skies.

Name: Sora Takenouchi (Adventure 2020)
Summary: Sora Takenouchi and Piyomon are main characters from Digimon Adventure 2020. Sora bears the crest of love, Piyomon is her partner Digimon. She is a "Chick" type Digimon who specializes in fire based attacks.

Name: Stakataka
Summary: Stakataka is a dual-type Rock/Steel Pokemon and is an Ultra Beast. It first appeared in the Alola Region in Pokemon Ultra Sun/Ultra Moon.

Name: Star Sapphire (DC Comics)
Summary: Carol Ferris was left in charge of the Ferris Aircraft Company after her father retired, leading to her hiring Hal Jordan as a test pilot. Though she secretly loved Hal (and Green Lantern), his status as an employee prevented her from dating him. At the same time, the alien Zamarons were desperate for a new queen, so they chose Carol. Though Carol did not want to leave Earth, the Zamarons brainwashed her into believing Green Lantern was an enemy and gave her the Star Sapphire Ring, causing her to become Star Sapphire.

Name: Starbrand (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Kevin Kale Connor was a no-name, constantly ignored college student until he was inadvertently granted the incredible power of the Star Brand by the Superflow of Earth-616. Overwhelmed by the Star Brand's might, Kevin accidentally destroyed the college he was attending, killing everyone on the premises. After clashing with the Avengers out of fear and confusion, he was taken by Nightmask to Ex Nihilio on Mars to learn to control his powers, becoming the hero Starbrand.

Name: Stardust
Summary: Lambda-Zero, known primarily by his herald name of Stardust, is a ruthless herald of Galactus and is probably the last surviving member of his race, the Ethereals, beings of pure energy.

Name: Storm (Marvel Comics)
Summary: nan

Name: Sunless
Summary: Sunless (or Sunny), is the main character of Shadow Slave. Growing up in the outskirts and leading a life of deceit and focusing on his own survival, he initially has a bleak outlook on life, even resigning himself to his fate when he was infected by the Nightmare Spell. But then, inside his First Nightmare, he resolved to himself that he must survive, no matter what.

Name: Superboy (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Superboy is the human/Kryptonian hybrid clone of Superman and Lex Luthor, created to be the ultimate living weapon.

Name: Supergirl (Post-Flashpoint)
Summary: Supergirl is a fictional superheroine appearing in comic books published by DC Comics and related media. The character was created by writer Otto Binder and designed by artist Al Plastino. Going by the real name Kara Zor-El, Supergirl is the biological cousin and female counterpart to DC Comic's iconic superhero Superman, created by writer Jerome Siegel and designed by artist Joseph Shuster.

Name: Superman (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Superman is one of the most powerful beings on Earth and its greatest hero. Born to the illustrious House of El, Kal-El is one of the last surviving members of his race as his planet was destroyed not long after his birth. He was found and raised by Jonathan and Martha Kent in Smallville, Kansas. Raised with high moral ideals, he uses his incredible strength, speed, flight and various other superpowers to fight evil and protect the innocent as a symbol of heroism and justice. In his civilian identity he is Clark Kent, a mild-mannered reporter working for the Daily Planet in Metropolis. Superman is also a founding member of the Justice League of America and a charter member of the Legion of Superheroes in the 30th Century.

Name: Superman (Rebirth)
Summary: Superman, also known as Clark Kent and Kal-El, is a Kryptonian superhero. Though born of the planet Krypton, he was sent away in a spaceship as a baby to save him from his home planet's destruction. His spaceship landed on Earth in Smallville, Kansas where he was found and adopted by Jonathan and Martha Kent. Raised to a high moral standard, Superman uses his powers to protect innocents and safeguard his adopted home. He is husband to Lois Lane and the father of Superboy.

Name: Taichi Yagami (Adventure 2020)
Summary: Taichi "Tai" Yagami and Agumon are main characters from the 2020 Reboot of Digimon Adventure. After being forcefully sucked into a Digital Space, Taichi meets Agumon alongside Yamato and Gabumon and defeats Algomon. Afterwards, Taichi and Co end up being sent to the Digital World where they go on an adventure to save the Holy Digimon while learning the secrets behind the Holy War between the forces of Light and Darkness.

Name: Takeru Takaishi (Adventure 2020)
Key: '''Takeru Takaishi''' | '''Patamon''' | '''Pegasusmon''' | '''Angemon''' | '''HolyAngemon''' / '''Holyangemon Priest Mode''' | '''Goddramon''' | '''Seraphimon and BlackSeraphimon''' | '''DanDevimon Shadow'''
Summary: Takeru and Patamon are main characters from Digimon Adventure 2020. Takeru is the crest bearer of Hope and the younger brother of Yamato Ishida.

Name: Tapu Bulu
Summary: Tapu Bulu is the guardian deity of Ula'ula Island.

Name: Tapu Fini
Summary: Tapu Fini is the Land Spirit Pokémon, and the guardian of Poni Island in the Alola Region. Tapu Fini has a black torso and light blue hair. It has a white headband-like marking on its head and a white v on its chest. To the sides of this V mark are two violet shell-like extensions from which protrude two arms with three fingers, separated in a way that would befit webbed arms such as those seen in Golduck. It has a fin at the lower front and does not appear to have legs, but an oval-shaped platform of sorts on which it stands. Its eyes have light blue eyeshadow-like marks and are light cyan with white eyebrows of sorts. Its shell is purple with a fin on top and a horn—when closed, this shell resembles a swordfish.

Name: Tapu Koko
Summary: Tapu Koko is the Guardian Deity of Melemele Island of the Alola region.

Name: Tapu Lele
Summary: Tapu Lele is the Psychic/Fairy Type guardian deity of Akala Island in the Alola Region. Tapu Lele is known for being unknowingly cruel as it loves spreading its scales which can heal others on the spot. However, too much of these scales can also destroy one's body. Its shell is supposed to be in the shape of a butterfly.

Name: Team Rocket Trio
Summary: ...and make it double!

Name: Terrakion
Summary: Terrakion is a Rock/Fighting Legendary Pokémon introduced in Pokémon Black and White. Terrakion, alongside Virizion, Cobalion and Keldeo, form the legendary group of Pokémon peacekeepers known as the Swords of Justice. Terrakion is physically the strongest of the group, and is said to be able to break down castle walls just by charging into them, according to legend.

Name: Terrax
Summary: Terrax the Tamer was once a petty tyrant of the city of Lanlak on the planet of Birj. A cruel person by nature, Galactus sought him as a herald, considering the failure of his previous herald to have been sympathy for inhabited planets. He bestowed upon Terrax a small portion of the Power Cosmic, giving him control over rock and earth on a massive scale, as well as his Cosmic Axe, a weapon capable of generating waves of force. He was later used as a pawn by both Annihilus and Doctor Doom after rebelling against Galactus.

Name: Thaal Sinestro (Post-Crisis)
Summary: Thaal Sinestro was once the greatest member of the Green Lantern Corps, being lauded by the Guardians of the Universe for his many deeds. He mentored and inspired many Green Lanterns, including Hal Jordan, who would later uncover Sinestro's more unsavory traits.

Name: Thanos (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Thanos, referred to as the Dark Lord by his most loyal underlings and the Mad Titan by the galactic community, is a powerful Titan warlord who rules over a distant region of space and commands two massive armies, known as the Chitauri and the Outriders, and a small group of followers known as the Black Order whom he adopted as his children. His main objective was to bring stability from the universe, as he believed its massive population would inevitably use up the universe's resources and condemn it. However, his methodology to succeed was warped; through the use of the ancient Infinity Stones, he intended to harness their power to exterminate half of all life in the universe, thus returning it to what he perceived to be a state of cosmic balance.

Name: The Hood (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The man who will become known as the Hood was originally a simple thug from the suburbs of New York City. His life was made of small crimes committed alongside his cousin John King, a relationship with a girl waiting their child and the preoccupations for his mentally-ill mother. Parker Robbins always aspired to be a supervillain and his career began when a would-be robbery turned into an encounter with a demon clad in red. Parker shot the monster down and looted it of its hood and boots. Upon realizing that these items bore magical powers, Parker finally saw the potential to satisfy his ambitions and began his journey to reach the top of the city's underworld.

Name: The Orb (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Ronan: Yes, that was our agreement. Bring you the Orb, and you will destroy Xandar for me. However, now that I know it contains an Infinity Stone, I wonder what use I have for you. Thanos: Boy, I would reconsider your current course. Korath: Master! You cannot! Thanos is the most powerful being in the universe. Ronan: Not anymore. You call me boy?! I will unfurl one thousand years of Kree justice on Xandar, and burn it to its core! Then, Thanos, I'm coming for you.

Name: Thor (Marvel Comics)
Key: '''Base Thor''' | '''Odinforce Thor''' | '''Herald of Thunder''' | '''Rune King Thor'''
Summary: Thor's death embodied as Thanos: The mortals do not care about you. Or even about themselves. At every turn, when faced with even a glimmer of light, they choose darkness. They cannot be saved, any more than Skurge can. They want to die. They want to kill everything else. That is what people are, Thor. A self-hating disease... Thor: No monster. That I will never accept. Thanos: How can you disagree when it is so self-evident? Why must you die for them now, Thor? They chose to kill the world. Don't they deserve to face the consequences? Thor: ... And what does a child deserve? What do they deserve who have fought tooth and nail? Who fight on still? Am I to surrender before they do? What would that make me? I say thee nay, nothing-believer. I say never. If there are but a thousand on the Earth who embrace the warmth in their souls--Who seek kindness, who share justice and love--I will fight for that thousand! If there are but a hundred, I will fight! If there are ten--I will fight! If there is only one soul remaining upon the whole Earth who knows love, I will battle to the end for that one! And they for me! To say otherwise is to give up! And I will not give up, Thanos. I cannot give up. We cannot give up.

Name: Thundurus
Summary: Thundurus is a member of the Forces of Nature of the Unova region in Pokémon Black/White and its sequels. Known and feared for his casual destructive nature, Thundurus is known as the "Bolt Strike" Pokémon.

Name: Tornadus
Summary: Tornadus is a Legendary Pokémon introduced in the Fifth Generation of Pokémon. He is a member of the "Forces of Nature" trio of Pokémon along with Landorus and Thundurus. Revered as a god among the people of Unova, Tornadus is an exceptionally powerful Flying Type Pokémon who is capable of generating severe storms.

Name: Type: Null
Summary: Type: Null, the Synthetic Pokémon, is a Normal-Type Pokémon introduced in Pokémon Sun and Moon. Type: Null was created for a mysterious purpose. In order for it to carry out its mission, its power is intended to rival that of Pokémon spoken of in myth. It was created from many different Pokémon so that it would be able to cope well with many different situations. The mask on Type: Null's head regulates its power, as well as hindering its agility with its great weight.

Name: Tyr Odinson (Marvel Comics)
Summary: What else but love of the realm and its citizens could have granted me the strength to sacrifice my very hand to the Fenris wolf--?

Name: Tyrannomon
Summary: Tier: 6-C | At least 6-C | 6-C | At least 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C | 3-C | 1-C

Name: Universal Weapon (Marvel Comics)
Summary: The Universal Weapon, also known as Cosmi-Rod, is one of the main weapons of the Kree race, being used by powerful Kree who managed to reach the highest rank in the Kree army, Supreme Accuser. It's most commonly known wielder is Ronan the Accuser, who made multiple appearances on Earth to enforce the Kree laws using the powers of of the weapon. It's currently being wielded by Lauri-Ell that is protecting the current emperor of the Kree/Skrull alliance Dorrek-Vell.

Name: Veigar
Summary: An enthusiastic master of dark sorcery, Veigar has embraced powers that few mortals dare approach. As a free-spirited inhabitant of Bandle City, he longed to push beyond the limitations of yordle magic, and turned instead to arcane texts that had been hidden away for thousands of years. Now a stubborn creature with an endless fascination for the mysteries of the universe, Veigar is often underestimated by others—but even though he believes himself truly evil, he possesses an inner morality that leads some to question his deeper motivations.

Name: Victini
Summary: Victini is a Fire/Psychic Mythical Pokémon, said to be the embodiment of victory, and resides in Liberty Garden. It is the star of Movie 14 along with the two primary members of the Tao Trio. It is unique in the fact that it's the only Pokémon that's not Grass type to begin a regional Pokedex, doubly so because it's an event Pokémon. It also controls the V-Wheel in Pokémon Mystery Dungeon: Gates of Infinity.

Name: Virizion
Summary: Pokédex entry in Pokémon White

Name: Vladimir
Summary: Tier: Low 7-C | At least 3-C, likely 3-B | Low 1-C

Name: Volcanicdramon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | 6-C | 3-C | Low 1-C | 1-C

Name: Volstagg (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Volstagg is an Asgardian and a friend of Thor, most notably being a member of the Warriors Three alongside Fandral and Hogun.

Name: Voyager (Marvel Comics)
Summary: Va Nee Gast was the daughter of the Grandmaster, one of the Elders of the Universe. She grew up exploring the cosmos by her father's side, taking part in his gambles and games, and learned from him in the process.

Name: Whirlwind (Skylanders)
Summary: Whirlwind is an air dragon with unicorn ancestry – two species that could not be more opposite in nature, which made her never quite fit in with either group. Other dragons were envious of her beauty, while unicorns shunned her for her ability to fly. But Whirlwind found peace within the dark and stormy clouds, where she learned to harness the tempest power within her. Despite her turbulent youth, she was the first to defend both dragons and unicorns when the trolls began hunting them, unleashing her ferocity in a brilliant and powerful rainbow that could be seen throughout many regions of Skylands. From that day forward, evil-doers would quake when dark clouds brewed, and run from the rainbow that followed the storm.

Name: Wisemon
Summary: Tier: High 8-C | At least High 8-C | 6-C | At least 6-C | At least 4-C, Possibly 3-C

Name: Witchmon
Summary: Tier: 6-C, 3-C on Halloween | At least 4-C, possibly 3-C, far higher on Halloween

Name: Xurkitree
Summary: Xurkitree, also known as UB-03 Lighting, is an Electric Type Pokémon introduced in Pokémon Sun and Moon. It is one of the Ultra Beasts appearing in the Alola region. It seems to be entirely made out of electric cables, and feeds on the earth's natural electricity.

Name: Yamato Ishida (Adventure 2020)
Summary: Yamato Ishida and Gabumon are main characters in the Digimon Adventure 2020. Yamato is the crest bearer of friendship and the older brother of Takeru Takaishi.

Name: Yveltal
Summary: Yveltal (Japanese: イベルタル Iberutaru) is a Dark/Flying Legendary Pokémon introduced in Generation VI. It is the mascot for Pokémon Y. It is Xerneas's counterpart.

Name: Zeraora
Summary: Zeraora is a Mythical Pokémon native to the Alola Region. Although it's unable to produce electricity on its own, Zeraora can absorb electricity from its environment to use Electric-type moves and create a magnetic field under its paws that allow it to tear its foes to pieces at the speed of lightning.

Name: Zeus (DC Comics)
Summary: Zeus is the King of the Olympian Gods, and one of the most powerful Cosmic Entities in the universe. He is more often than not a neutral being, rarely interfering with mortal affairs and only acting if the threat proves great enough.

Name: Zygarde
Summary: Zygarde is a Dragon/Ground Type Legendary Pokémon introduced in Generation VI. It's hypothesized that it's monitoring those who destroy the ecosystem from deep in the cave where it lives. When the Kalos region's ecosystem falls into disarray, it appears and reveals its secret power.

Name: Aether (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: The Reality Stone is one of the six Infinity Stones, the remnant of a singularity that predated the universe, which represents the fabric of reality. Liquefied into a dark red fluid called the Aether (pronounced ēTHər), the Dark Elves and their leader Malekith intended to use it to revert the universe to its state of primordial darkness. The Aether was taken from the Elves by the Asgardians and entrusted to the Collector following the Second Dark Elf Conflict.

Name: Alder
Summary: Alder (アデク Adeku) is the Champion of the Unova region's Pokémon League in Pokémon Black and White.

Name: Arishem (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Arishem the Judge is the Prime Celestial, who is credited for causing the Big Bang, creating the universe, and bringing light to the universe, ending the Ginnungagap. He is the first of the Celestials, who came before the very dawn of creation, and their leader. Millions of years ago, Arishem created the Deviants in order to aid in Celestial births, but when his creations went rogue, the Judge created the race of Eternals using the World Forge, in order to combat the Deviants who were interfering in his work.

Name: Ash Ketchum
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Original Series)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Advance Generation through Best Wishes)''' | '''Pokémon Team (XY)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Sun and Moon)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Journeys)'''
Summary: Ash Ketchum (Japanese: サトシ Satoshi) is the main character of the original Pokémon anime. He is also the main character of various manga based on the anime, including The Electric Tale of Pikachu, Ash & Pikachu, Magical Pokémon Journey, and Pocket Monsters Diamond & Pearl, including some direct adaptations like the Pokémon Journeys manga.

Name: AZ (Pokémon)
Summary: AZ is an important backstory character of Pokémon X & Y. 3,000 years prior, AZ was the King of the Kalos region, at the same time as the war. His Floette was forcibly introduced in the conflict, causing its death. In grief, and in an attempt to revive his lost companion, he built the Ultimate Weapon, which ultimately ended the war, and made him immortal.

Name: Bewear (Anime)
Summary: Bewear (Japanese: キテルグマ Kiteruguma) is a reoccurring Pokémon character in the anime. She appears to have appointed herself as Team Rocket's caretaker during their stay in the Alola region.

Name: Blacephalon
Summary: Blacephalon is an Ultra Beast, designated as UB: Burst. It is a humanoid Ultra Beast from another dimension. It is obsessed with explosions and constantly blows up its own head to surprise others so it can distract them and rob them of their vitality.

Name: Buzzwole
Summary: Buzzwole is one of the Ultra Beasts that appeared in the Alola region. It is the Sun counterpart of Pheromosa. Buzzwole is an Ultra Beast that resembles a large mosquito. Its size makes it the heaviest Bug-type Pokémon. Its head is small and flat with a black ridge up the center. It has two red compound eyes with two black, spherical basal joints for its red and black antennae between them. Protruding from under these joints is a long, silver proboscis. Buzzwole debuted in A Mission of Ultra Urgency!, where it appeared through an Ultra Wormhole at Melemele Meadow. It was the first Ultra Beast that Ash and his classmates were tasked to capture and return to its home world as the Ultra Guardians. Ash eventually succeeded in catching Buzzwole with a Beast Ball, allowing it to be returned home through another Ultra Wormhole soon after.

Name: Captain Marvel (Carol Danvers)
Summary: nan

Name: Celesteela
Summary: Celesteela is a dual-type Steel/Flying Pokémon introduced in Pokémon Sun and Moon. It is one of the Ultra Beasts, which were briefly found in Alola following the Aether Foundation Incident. It is the second heaviest Pokémon to date.

Name: Cheren (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Early Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (End Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Post-Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Gym Battle)'''
Summary: Cheren, "The one who seeks the right path" is a main character in Pokémon Black/White and its sequel, Pokémon Black/White 2. Cheren, Bianca and Hilbert all went off on their Pokémon journey on the same day and thus their individual journeys intersected quite often, with Cheren occasionally finding himself duking it out with Hilbert and fighting by his side against Team Plasma. Though Cheren sometimes comes off as cold and distant, he's actually a good hearted and very honest person who seeks to do the right thing. He is also very smart and knowledgeable about Pokémon.

Name: Cobalion
Summary: Cobalion is a Legendary Steel/Fighting-type Pokémon and the de facto leader of the Swords of Justice. Known as the Iron Will Pokémon, this stern and composed Pokémon defends its brethren from human encroachment and abuse across the Unova region and pacifies the unruliest Pokémon with a single glare. It can be equally harsh with its allies, being the disciplinarian and mentor to the group's newest edition, Keldeo, but nevertheless cares for others despite its unapproachable exterior.

Name: Diancie
Summary: Diancie is a Rock/Fairy Mythical Pokémon that was introduced in Gen VI.

Name: Diantha
Summary: Diantha is an actress and the Champion of the Kalos region.

Name: Drasna
Summary: nan

Name: Faba
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''First Fights Teams''' | '''Pokémon Team (Post Game/Title Defense)'''
Summary: Faba is the Branch Chief of the Aether Foundation and the foundation's "last line of defense".

Name: Fingolfin
Summary: Fingolfin was the second High King of the Ñoldor in Beleriand, the Ñoldor being one of the three branches of Elves. He was the eldest son of Finwë and Indis, younger brother of Findis, older brother of Irimë and Finarfin, and the younger half-brother of Fëanor. He founded the House of Fingolfin, which ruled the Ñoldor in Middle-earth. His wife was Anairë and his children were Fingon, Turgon, Aredhel, and Argon. Fingolfin was said to be the strongest, most steadfast, and most valiant of Finwë's sons, although this is contradicted by other statements naming Feanor as the strongest Elf of all time.

Name: Fëanor
Summary: Fëanor was an Elda of the Ñoldor, and one of the Elven kindred that departed Valinor in the land of Aman, where they had lived with the angelic spirits known as the Valar. Fëanor was born in Valinor, the only child of Finwë, the High King of the Ñoldor, and Finwë's first wife Míriel Therindë. He is renowned as a craftsman, gem-smith, and warrior, the maker of the Silmarils and inventor of the Tengwar script. He was also the creator of the seven Palantíri. He was considered the greatest of the Eldar in arts and lore and the most powerful among them but also the proudest and most self-willed.

Name: Gandalf
Key: '''Gandalf the Grey''' | '''Gandalf the White''' | '''Within the confines of Eä''' | '''Prior to entering Eä'''
Summary: Gandalf, originally known as Olórin, is a member of the order of wizards known as the Istari. Despite his appearance, Gandalf is not a human sorcerer, but rather a Maia of the ancient race of beings known as the Ainur, who existed before the creation of Arda. He is one of the main heroes in both J.R.R Tolkien's Middle-Earth saga and Peter Jackson's live-action adaptation of the books respectively.

Name: Genesect
Summary: Genesect is a bipedal, insectoid Pokémon with a metal body and a saucer-shaped head. It is primarily purple with several gray markings. It has two large red eyes and a small white part that could be either its mouth or a vent. It has thin arms with overlapping segments. Each arm ends with a single, pointed claw. There is a gray circle on each shoulder, and a gray band around its abdomen. Its segmented legs each end with a large, upward curving claw.

Name: Ghetsis
Summary: Ghetsis Harmonia (Japanese: ゲーチス・ハルモニア G-Cis Harmonia) is one of the Seven Sages, the true mastermind behind Team Plasma and the primary antagonist in Black, White, Black 2, and White 2.

Name: Gladion
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokèmon Team (Route 5)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Aether Paradise)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Mount Lanakila)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Pokémon League)'''
Summary: Gladion is a former member of the Aether Foundation and the son of Lusamine. He originally lived in harmony with his family in Aether Paradise until he noted his mother's obsession with the Ultra Beasts. Realizing the Ultra Beasts would bring ruin to Alola should they be released, Gladion left the foundation and stole one of their Type: Nulls. He then set out to stop Lusamine and free his Type: Null from its mask while working as an enforcer of Team Skull.

Name: Guzma
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Malie Garden)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Shady House)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Aether Paradise)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Hau'oli City, Team Rocket's Castle and Title Defense)'''
Summary: Guzma (Japanese: グズマ Guzma) is the leader of Team Skull.

Name: Guzzlord
Summary: Guzzlord is one of the many Ultra Beasts in the Pokémon Sun & Moon game. It seems to be a big eater, as shown by its Pokédex entries.

Name: Hoopa
Summary: Hoopa is the Dual Ghost/Psychic-type Pokémon who is known as the Mischievous Pokémon and the Djinn Pokémon. Known for its ability to open holes in hyperspace, it frequently plays harmless pranks on others with its abilities for its own amusement. However, should the Prison Bottle, an artifact created to seal the full extent of Hoopa's powers, be unsealed or destroyed, Hoopa will become Hoopa Unbound, an avaricious entity filled with malice who wreaks havoc by summoning powerful Pokémon from across space and time.

Name: Infinity Gauntlet (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: The Infinity Stones are the condensed remains of six Singularities that existed long before the current universe. Every Stone holds a power so vast that it lies beyond mortal comprehension. Each controls a primordial aspect of the universe: space, reality, time, power, mind, and soul.

Name: Iris (Pokémon)
Summary: Iris is a trainer from Unova. Originally one of the two gym leaders for Opelucid City, she became the champion of the Unova league after extensive training from Drayden.

Name: Kartana
Summary: Kartana is one of the Ultra Beasts from the Alola region.

Name: Keldeo
Summary: Keldeo is a dual-type Water/Fighting Mythical Pokémon.

Name: Landorus
Summary: Landorus is a Legendary Pokémon introduced in the Fifth Generation of Pokémon. He is a member of and the master of the "Forces of Nature". Landorus is considered the "Guardian of the Fields", due to helping crops grow. His tail causes the soil to gain nutrition.

Name: Lunala
Summary: Lunala (Japanese: ルナアーラ Lunala) is a Psychic/Ghost-type Legendary Pokémon.

Name: Lusamine
Key: '''By Herself''' | '''Pokémon Team''' | '''Merged Lusamine''' | '''Pokémon Team (Post-Merge Lusamine)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Title Defense)'''
Summary: Lusamine is the current president of the Aether Foundation, an organization created to shelter Pokémon from villainous organizations like Team Skull and nurse these Pokémon back to health to be returned to the wild. She is the insane and corrupt president of the Aether Foundation, who not only abuses her own children and has performed various gruesome experiments on the very Pokemon she's supposed to take care of and protect but also plans to go to Ultra Space to reach the Ultra Beasts, even if it means unleashing their fury on the Alola region.

Name: Lysandre
Summary: Lysandre (Japanese: フラダリ Fuladari) is the leader of Team Flare and the main antagonist of Pokémon X and Y. Formerly the student of Professor Sycamore, he later went on to found Lysandre Labs and create the Holo Caster. At some point in the future, Lysandre was convinced of humanity's stupidity and became misanthropic, generating his desire to wipe the world of all humans and Pokémon not affiliated with Team Flare through the use of his ancestor's Ultimate Weapon. However, thanks to the efforts of Calem/Serena, he is stopped right before the weapon’s activation, but even after their attempts to convince him that the world is not as bad as he thinks, Lysandre rejects the idea and tries to kill them by detonating the Ultimate Weapon with what little power remains in it. While Calem/Serena escape the explosion, Lysandre is presumed dead and Team Flare disbands.

Name: Lúthien
Summary: Lúthien was an half-elven, half-Maia, born to king Thingol and Melian. Her bloodline passed far down the lines of both Elves and Men, in both the kings of Númenor and then the kingdoms of Arnor and Gondor after, with both the maiden Arwen and the king of Gondor in the beginning of the Fourth Era, Aragorn, claiming descendance from her and Beren.

Name: Magearna
Summary: nan

Name: Malekith (Marvel Cinematic Universe)
Summary: Malekith is the primary antagonist of Thor: The Dark World. He is the leader of the Dark Elves of Svartalfheim, having led them into battle against King Bor and the Asgardians five thousand years ago. At the end of that conflict, he and his race were defeated and entered a state of suspended animation within one of their warships until the Aether resurfaced, awakening them. Malekith and the Dark Elves sacked Asgard in their quest to reclaim the Aether and use its reality-warping power together with the phenomenon known as the Convergence to transform all matter in the universe into dark matter. However, despite Malekith's best efforts, the Dark Elves were again defeated by Thor and his companions.

Name: Manwë
Key: '''Within the confines of Eä''' | '''Prior to entering Eä'''
Summary: Manwë is the Elder King of Arda and brethren to Melkor in the mind of Eru Ilúvatar. He is said to be the one that best understands the will and designs of Eru, and acted as the chief instrument against Melkor's discourse during the second theme of the Ainulindalë, the Great Music. Manwë would later come to lead the Ainur loyal to Eru against Melkor's ambitions over the world, leading to many of the events that defined the Silmarillion, with the conflict ultimately concluding with Melkor's defeat in the War of Wrath, afterwhich he would be cast through the Door of Night into the Void beyond Eä, bound in the great chain Angainor.

Name: Meltan
Summary: Melmetal is the evolutionary form of Meltan.

Name: Meowth (Team Rocket)
Summary: Meowth is a Member of the Team rocket Trio. Upon being abandoned on a box by his mother as a baby, he was forced to take care of himself on the streets, eventually learning how to talk and walk on 2 legs to impress a female meowth. Upon repeated failures and crimes committed, he was approached by team rocket and found his goal in life, being Giovanni's own pet to obtain a father figure, besides achieving wealth and power.

Name: Mew (Pokémon)
Summary: Mew is a Psychic Type Mythical Pokémon. It is said to be the progenitor of all other Pokémon and was the base for Mewtwo's genetic code.

Name: Mewtwo
Summary: Mewtwo is a Psychic-type Legendary Pokémon. The story of Mewtwo has quite a few versions, but they all start off the same. Before Mewtwo, there was Mew, the ancestor of all Pokémon.

Name: Morgoth
Key: '''Following his corruption of Eä '''| '''Within the confines of Eä''' | '''Prior to entering Eä'''
Summary: Morgoth, (Sindarin for "Dark Tyrant" or the "Dark Foe"), originally known as Melkor (Quenya for "He who arises in might"), is the primary antagonist of The Silmarillion. He was once the greatest of the Ainur, servants and creations of the Creator, Eru Ilúvatar, before becoming the first Dark Lord out of jealousy of his creator's power, the Secret Fire, the creator's ability to create true life and free will.

Name: N (Pokémon)
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Early Game)''' | '''Pokémon Team (End Game)''' | '''Black and White 2''' | '''Pokémon Team (Season Battles)'''
Summary: N is a character in Black, White, Black 2, and White 2. He was the puppet leader of Team Plasma in Pokémon Black and White and aspired to create separate worlds for humans and Pokémon. His full name is Natural Harmonia Gropius (ナチュラル・ハルモニア・グロピウス Natural Harmonia Gropius).

Name: Necrozma
Summary: Necrozma is a Pokémon that has only been found in the Alola region. It has characteristics similar to that of the Ultra Beasts and is said to have come from another world in ancient times. It normally lies inert underground, but it awakens violently and painfully in the presence of light, which it devours as a source of energy.

Name: Nihilego
Summary: Nihilego, also known as UB-01 Symbiont, is a dual-type Rock/Poison Pokémon introduced in Pokémon Sun and Moon. It is one of the Ultra Beasts and is among the first to be seen in the game. It particularly seems to be the object of Lusamine's affection.

Name: Pheromosa
Summary: Pheromosa, also known as UB-02 Beauty, is a dual-type Bug/Fighting Pokémon introduced in Pokémon Sun and Moon. It is one of the mysterious "Ultra Beasts" of the Alola region. It first appeared following the Aether Foundation incident.

Name: Pikachu (Anime)
Key: '''Original Series-Best Wishes Series''' | '''XY Series '''| '''Sun & Moon Series Onwards '''| '''Blue Orb Absorbed''' | '''Gigantamax'''
Summary: Pikachu is Ash Ketchum's main Pokémon from the Pokémon anime. Originally a reluctant member of Ash's team, when the young boy tried to save Pikachu's life from a flock of Spearow, he warmed up to Ash, and ever since then, he remained an invaluable member of Ash's team, going through thick and thin to help Ash achieve his dream of being the very best.

Name: Pikachu (PokéPark)
Key: '''Meadow Zone''' | '''Beach Zone to Flower Zone''' | '''End of PokéPark''' | '''PokéPark 2''' | '''End of PokéPark 2'''
Summary: Pikachu is one of Mew’s four best friends, and the protagonist of the PokéPark duology. Having lived and played with Mew, one day a hole opened up in the ground, and caused him to accidentally fall into a land called PokéPark. He learned that friendship there was basically dying, and as a result the Sky Prism had partially shattered, which could have eventually led to the Sky Pavilion falling on the PokéPark itself. Mew took this as an opportunity to test his friend and save PokéPark at the same time, manipulating events so that specific people, such as those running Attractions, came to find or were given the shards of the Sky Prism that Pikachu needed. Over the course of the game Pikachu gets stronger, tougher, and grows far beyond he ever thought possible, as he gains each Sky Prism shard and even saves the Park itself.

Name: Plumeria
Key: '''By Herself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Akala Outskirts)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Route 15)''' | '''Pokémon Team (Title Defense)'''
Summary: Plumeria is an admin of Team Skull who seems to specialize in Poison-type Pokémon. Due to her actions she is considered a "sisterly figure" to the organization.

Name: Poipole
Summary: Poipole is one of the many Ultra Beasts. It was seen as owned by the Ultra Recon Squad. It is apparently seen as a starter, much like Bulbasaur or Charmander in their world. Despite this, the Pokémon is capable of holding off Pokémon who are easily far stronger than said starters.

Name: Ryuki
Key: '''By Himself''' | '''Pokémon Team (Malie City)''' | '''Post-Game and Title Defense Team'''
Summary: Ryuki (Japanese: リュウキ Ryūki) is a non-player character in the Generation VII games, Pokémon Sun and Moon. He is a Pokémon Trainer who specializes in Dragon-type Pokémon.

Name: Solgaleo
Summary: Solgaleo is a Psychic/Steel Legendary Pokémon native to the Alola region. Honored and feared as the "beast that devours the sun", Solgaleo is known for its incredible power and its striking mane that can light up the darkest of night skies.

Name: Stakataka
Summary: Stakataka is a dual-type Rock/Steel Pokemon and is an Ultra Beast. It first appeared in the Alola Region in Pokemon Ultra Sun/Ultra Moon.

Name: Sunless
Summary: Sunless (or Sunny), is the main character of Shadow Slave. Growing up in the outskirts and leading a life of deceit and focusing on his own survival, he initially has a bleak outlook on life, even resigning himself to his fate when he was infected by the Nightmare Spell. But then, inside his First Nightmare, he resolved to himself that he must survive, no matter what.

Name: Tapu Bulu
Summary: Tapu Bulu is the guardian deity of Ula'ula Island.

Name: Tapu Fini
Summary: Tapu Fini is the Land Spirit Pokémon, and the guardian of Poni Island in the Alola Region. Tapu Fini has a black torso and light blue hair. It has a white headband-like marking on its head and a white v on its chest. To the sides of this V mark are two violet shell-like extensions from which protrude two arms with three fingers, separated in a way that would befit webbed arms such as those seen in Golduck. It has a fin at the lower front and does not appear to have legs, but an oval-shaped platform of sorts on which it stands. Its eyes have light blue eyeshadow-like marks and are light cyan with white eyebrows of sorts. Its shell is purple with a fin on top and a horn—when closed, this shell resembles a swordfish.

Name: Tapu Koko
Summary: Tapu Koko is the Guardian Deity of Melemele Island of the Alola region.

Name: Tapu Lele
Summary: Tapu Lele is the Psychic/Fairy Type guardian deity of Akala Island in the Alola Region. Tapu Lele is known for being unknowingly cruel as it loves spreading its scales which can heal others on the spot. However, too much of these scales can also destroy one's body. Its shell is supposed to be in the shape of a butterfly.

Name: Team Rocket Trio
Summary: ...and make it double!

Name: Terrakion
Summary: Terrakion is a Rock/Fighting Legendary Pokémon introduced in Pokémon Black and White. Terrakion, alongside Virizion, Cobalion and Keldeo, form the legendary group of Pokémon peacekeepers known as the Swords of Justice. Terrakion is physically the strongest of the group, and is said to be able to break down castle walls just by charging into them, according to legend.

Name: Thundurus
Summary: Thundurus is a member of the Forces of Nature of the Unova region in Pokémon Black/White and its sequels. Known and feared for his casual destructive nature, Thundurus is known as the "Bolt Strike" Pokémon.

Name: Tornadus
Summary: Tornadus is a Legendary Pokémon introduced in the Fifth Generation of Pokémon. He is a member of the "Forces of Nature" trio of Pokémon along with Landorus and Thundurus. Revered as a god among the people of Unova, Tornadus is an exceptionally powerful Flying Type Pokémon who is capable of generating severe storms.

Name: Type: Null
Summary: Type: Null, the Synthetic Pokémon, is a Normal-Type Pokémon introduced in Pokémon Sun and Moon. Type: Null was created for a mysterious purpose. In order for it to carry out its mission, its power is intended to rival that of Pokémon spoken of in myth. It was created from many different Pokémon so that it would be able to cope well with many different situations. The mask on Type: Null's head regulates its power, as well as hindering its agility with its great weight.

Name: Victini
Summary: Victini is a Fire/Psychic Mythical Pokémon, said to be the embodiment of victory, and resides in Liberty Garden. It is the star of Movie 14 along with the two primary members of the Tao Trio. It is unique in the fact that it's the only Pokémon that's not Grass type to begin a regional Pokedex, doubly so because it's an event Pokémon. It also controls the V-Wheel in Pokémon Mystery Dungeon: Gates of Infinity.

Name: Virizion
Summary: Pokédex entry in Pokémon White

Name: Xurkitree
Summary: Xurkitree, also known as UB-03 Lighting, is an Electric Type Pokémon introduced in Pokémon Sun and Moon. It is one of the Ultra Beasts appearing in the Alola region. It seems to be entirely made out of electric cables, and feeds on the earth's natural electricity.

Name: Yveltal
Summary: Yveltal (Japanese: イベルタル Iberutaru) is a Dark/Flying Legendary Pokémon introduced in Generation VI. It is the mascot for Pokémon Y. It is Xerneas's counterpart.

Name: Zeraora
Summary: Zeraora is a Mythical Pokémon native to the Alola Region. Although it's unable to produce electricity on its own, Zeraora can absorb electricity from its environment to use Electric-type moves and create a magnetic field under its paws that allow it to tear its foes to pieces at the speed of lightning.

Name: Zygarde
Summary: Zygarde is a Dragon/Ground Type Legendary Pokémon introduced in Generation VI. It's hypothesized that it's monitoring those who destroy the ecosystem from deep in the cave where it lives. When the Kalos region's ecosystem falls into disarray, it appears and reveals its secret power.

Name: Gumball Watterson
Summary: My brain is amazing; when I find something boring, it actually prevents me from hearing it.

Name: Jedah Dohma
Summary: Jedah is one of the three High Nobles of the Makai, a realm of demons under the leadership of his fellow high noble Belial Aensland. But Jedah suffered a messiah complex as he believed that Belial's rule would stagnate the Makai and sought to overthrow him when the opportune moment presents itself. Tricked by his confident Ozom into absorbing the energies of a Makai Gate for his agenda, Jedah ended up being destroyed in the process with his body reconstituted a century later. Seeing what the Makai had became in his absence, creating the Majigen pocket dimension to enact his plan to lure those he considered worthy, Jedah convinced himself that he must wipe out all realms of existence and fuse all souls into a single perfect being: the Shintai.

Name: King Boo
Summary: King Boo is the leader of the Boos and the main antagonist of the Luigi's Mansion series and is the arch-nemesis of Luigi. He is also an ally of Bowser, who has aided him in his various schemes. He is more than capable of devising and enacting villainous plans by himself, including his capture and imprisonment of Mario. Although not the biggest Boo, King Boo has abilities that far surpass that of the average ghost and he wields a number of impressive magical abilities, including the ability to materialize objects. King Boo's magical power is directly proportional to the number of Boos in his vicinity.

Name: Soul King
Summary: Adnyeus (アドナイェウス, Adonayeusu?), more commonly known as the Soul King (霊れい王おう, Reiō?), is the king of Soul Society, whose existence in Soul Society is as symbolic as it is absolute.
